article.headline: Yarde, Fitz help power Marist past Niagara
article.linkText: Marist uses balanced scoring to crush Niagara
article.story:
POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Brandy Gang and Julianne Viani scored 16 points each, leading Marist (Not ranked ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) to a 98-51 victory over Niagara on Friday night.

Corielle Yarde had 15 points and six assists, and Rachele Fitz added 11 points -- reaching double digits for the 48th straight game -- and eight rebounds for the Red Foxes (14-1, 5-0 Metro Atlantic Conference).

Liz Flooks scored 14 points for Niagara (1-14, 0-4), which shot 2-for-15 from the 3-point line.

Every player made a field goal for Marist, which shot 23-for-26 on free throws and had 24 assists on 31 field goals.
